  description: "The \\Item[Stone Sceptre of Shih]{Stone Sceptre} has been recovered! But will it be enough to stop the \\NPC{Raja of Solon}? \\NPC{Ambuchar Devayam} has massed 10\'000 zombies on \\Place{Ra-Khati}\'s border. Only \\NPC{Gaumahavi}, the \\NPC[Gaumahavi]{Great Dragon of the Purple Wastes}, stands between him and the \\Place{Hidden Kingdom}. Yet even she cannot face \\NPC[Ambuchar Devayam]{Ambuchar} alone, for the evil \\NPC[Raja of Solon]{raja} has recovered an archaic \\Group{Imaskari} relic that renders him invincible. If \\Place{Ra-Khati} is to be saved and the player characters are to escape the \\NPC[Raja of Solon]{raja}\'s curse., \\NPC{Ambuchar Devayam} must be stopped. But how? The player characters\' search for a solution will embroil them in \\Place[Tuiga]{Tuigan} politics, lure them to the \\Place{Red Mountain Monastery}\'s forbidden halls, and lead them into ancient \\Place{Solon} itself, where \\NPC[Ambuchar Devayam]{Ambuchar}\'s slaves---both living and undead---toil to make him even more dangerous. \\Product[TSR 9304]{Blood Charge} is the third adventure in the \\Product{Empires Adventures Trilogy}, taking place in the new \\Place{Forgotten Realms} campaign world territories described in \\Product[TSR 1055]{The Horde} campaign set. The \\Product{Empires Adventures Trilogy} is set amidst the turbulent events portrayed in the \\Product{Empires Novel Trilogy}. This adventure is designed for four to eight player characters of level 7--10. It can be played as a separate, stand-alone module or as the sequel to FRA2, \\Product[TSR 9290]{Black Courser}. Look for the other \\Product[Empires Adventures Trilogy]{Empires Adventures}: Product[TSR 9281]{Storm Riders} and \\Product[TSR 9290]{Black Courser}!"
